[thinking] I’m considering what happens if the native operation succeeds. If it defines a class that's unsupported, it could throw an UnsupportedOperationException. The rule here is to catch Errors, but we also currently catch Exceptions. We could look into both to understand the cause better. There might be issues with the class initialization of AbstractClassLoader, especially if the static block uses AccessController or if Class.forName is involved during the native build or runtime.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Considering ClassFilter**
[thinking] 
